<subSubSection id="B88331D9FF98FF6FB5E63DDB22910836" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F0266252FF98FF6FB5E63DDB22910836" blockId="2.[136,1452,1700,2051]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF98FF6FB5E63DDB2132068A" author="Bentham, G." box="[136,320,1700,1726]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" pagination="226 - 228" refId="ref7178" refString="Bentham, G. (1870) Caesalpinieae. In: von Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora Brasiliensis 15 (2). F. Fleischer, Leipzig, pp. 226 - 228." type="book chapter" year="1870">Bentham (1870)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF98FF6FB4D23DDA2256068A" box="[444,548,1700,1726]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bijuga">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF98FF6FB4D23DDA2256068A" box="[444,548,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">E. bijuga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on Martius’ collections from two localities: “insulam 
<location id="F5463489FF98FF6FB1BA3DDB255A068A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF98FF6FB5E63EF722910836:F5463489FF98FF6FB1BA3DDB255A068A" box="[1236,1320,1700,1726]" country="Brazil" county="Bentham" municipality="Herbarium Hookerianum" name="Marajo" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" stateProvince="Tocantins">Marajo</location>
” and “ostia fl. 
<collectingRegion id="325DACB0FF98FF6FB5C63DB7216906D6" box="[168,283,1736,1762]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
”. One collection is found at K, one at LE, one at L, and six at 
<collectorName id="5D6C0784FF98FF6FB6873DB6244606D6" box="[1001,1076,1736,1763]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">M. All</collectorName>
collections are from “ 
<location id="F5463489FF98FF6FB05F3DB720850732" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF98FF6FB5E63EF722910836:F5463489FF98FF6FB05F3DB720850732" country="Brazil" county="Bentham" municipality="Herbarium Hookerianum" name="Provinciae Paraensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" stateProvince="Tocantins">Provinciae Paraënsis</location>
”, the current state of Pará, 
<collectingCountry id="888E22C2FF98FF6FB77B3D93222F0732" box="[533,605,1772,1798]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.Most of them are from “insulam 
<location id="F5463489FF98FF6FB6A83D9324680732" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF98FF6FB5E63EF722910836:F5463489FF98FF6FB6A83D9324680732" box="[966,1050,1772,1798]" country="Brazil" county="Bentham" municipality="Herbarium Hookerianum" name="Marajo" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" stateProvince="Tocantins">Marajo</location>
” (K, LE, M[0215266], M[0215267], and M[0215268]), one from “ostia fl. 
<collectingRegion id="325DACB0FF98FF6FB7263C6F22C6071E" box="[584,692,1808,1834]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
et 
<location id="F5463489FF98FF6FB7B33C6F2311071E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF98FF6FB5E63EF722910836:F5463489FF98FF6FB7B33C6F2311071E" box="[733,867,1808,1834]" country="Brazil" county="Bentham" municipality="Herbarium Hookerianum" name="Amazonum" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" stateProvince="Tocantins">Amazonum</location>
” (M[0215265]), and one from ad “ 
<location id="F5463489FF98FF6FB06E3C6F25D0071E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF98FF6FB5E63EF722910836:F5463489FF98FF6FB06E3C6F25D0071E" box="[1280,1442,1808,1834]" country="Brazil" county="Bentham" municipality="Herbarium Hookerianum" name="Canalem Jabi" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" stateProvince="Tocantins">Canalem Jabi</location>
” (M[0215269]). 
<collectorName id="5D6C0784FF98FF6FB4593C4B210D077B" box="[311,383,1844,1871]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">The K</collectorName>
exsiccate has a donation stamp “ 
<collectingMunicipality id="1042F828FF98FF6FB7943C4B246B077A" box="[762,1049,1844,1870]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">Herbarium Hookerianum</collectingMunicipality>
1867” and a label from Herbarium Regium Monacense (M herbarium). All collections at M have the same label with a stamp “vid 
<collectingCounty id="19471ADEFF98FF6FB19E3C2725270746" box="[1264,1365,1880,1906]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">Bentham</collectingCounty>
1869”. 
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF98FF6FB5E63C03215B07A3" author="Cowan, R. S." box="[136,297,1916,1943]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref7339" refString="Cowan, R. S. (1975) Monograph of the genus Eperua (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 28: 1 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 0081024 X. 28" type="journal article" year="1975">Cowan (1975)</bibRefCitation>
described the K exsiccate as the 
<typeStatus id="2F22DCF0FF98FF6FB7F33C03228D07A2" box="[669,767,1916,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">holotype</typeStatus>
and those at M as isotypes. However, the fact that one of the type locations - “ 
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF98FF6FB4293CDE22D9078E" box="[327,683,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">
ostia fl. 
<location id="F5463489FF98FF6FB4CE3CDE218C078E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF98FF6FB5E63EF722910836:F5463489FF98FF6FB4CE3CDE218C078E" box="[416,510,1953,1978]" country="Brazil" municipality="Amazonum" name="Tocantis" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" stateProvince="Tocantins">Tocantis</location>
et 
<collectingMunicipality id="1042F828FF98FF6FB7713CDF22D0078E" box="[543,674,1952,1978]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">Amazonum</collectingMunicipality>
”
</emphasis>
- is restricted to one of the M exsiccates indicates that Bentham used the M exsiccates to describe 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF98FF6FB4BB3CBA224C07EA" box="[469,574,1988,2014]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bijuga">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF98FF6FB4BB3CBA224C07EA" box="[469,574,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">E. bijuga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, these three unnumbered collections of 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF98FF6FB1E83CBB24AF07EA" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1846" box="[1158,1245,1988,2014]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Martius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="2" pageNumber="191" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Martius</taxonomicName>
are 
<typeStatus id="2F22DCF0FF98FF6FB07F3CBA250407EB" box="[1297,1398,1989,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">syntypes</typeStatus>
, and here we correct Cowan’s use of 
<typeStatus id="2F22DCF0FF98FF6FB4813C9722230836" box="[495,593,2024,2050]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">holotype</typeStatus>
to 
<typeStatus id="2F22DCF0FF98FF6FB71B3C9722AD0836" box="[629,735,2024,2050]" pageId="2" pageNumber="191">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
